# Learning Log

Use this log to track important decisions, discoveries, and learnings during development.

## Log Reference

@docs/learning-log.md

## When to Update the Log

- After making significant architectural decisions
- When discovering new patterns or approaches
- When solving complex problems
- When making design trade-offs

## Log Entry Format

**Timestamp | Context | Decision | Rationale | Impact**

Keep entries short and structured for LLM consumption, not human readability.

## Usage

The agent can request this rule when:
- Documenting significant decisions
- Reflecting on development progress
- Looking up past decisions
- Planning future work based on learnings
